<title type="html"><![CDATA[Pac-Man demo changes slightly after game reset]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12181&amp;p=138252#p138252"><![CDATA[
Load the Famicom port of Pac-Man (1984) into any emulator and study the game demo.  Normally, Pac-man just misses consuming Blinky (the red ghost) and is ultimately killed by Inky (the cyan ghost).  However, after a (soft) game reset, the demo changes slightly: Pac-Man manages to consume Blinky (the red ghost) and is ultimately killed by Pinky (the pink ghost).  <br /><br />Any ideas on why the demo changes after a reset?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6828">zeroone</a> — Mon Dec 29, 2014 2:02 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
